author.name: Niẓāmī Ganjavī, 1140 or 41-1202 or 3
Ilyās ibn Yūsuf Niẓāmī Ganjavī
الياس بن يوسف نظامى گنجوى
Author dates preferred by cataloger: d. 605 AH / 1209 CE

notesStmt.note: This illuminated and illustrated Safavid copy of the Khamsah (quintet) of Niẓāmī Ganjavī (d. 605 AH / 1209 CE) dates to the eleventh century AH / seventeenth CE. The codex opens with a double-page illuminated frontispiece (fols. 1b-2a). Each of the five poems begins with an illuminated headpiece (fols. 32b, 117b, 176b, 240b, 331b), and there are thirty-six illustrations. The lacquer binding is not original to the manuscript.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Persian.

msItem.title: Khamsah-i Niẓāmī
خمسه نظامى
msItem.incipit: بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم هست كليد در كنج حكيم...
msItem.note: Contains: Makhzan al-asrār (fols. 1b-31b); Khusraw va Shīrīn (fols. 32b-117a); Laylá va Majnūn (fols. 117b-176a); Haft paykar (fols. 176b-240a); and Iskandarnāmah, divided into Sharafnāmah (fols. 240b-331a) and Iqbālnāmah (fols. 331b-380a); title of each poem not indicated; some folios supplied later
